{"repo": "buildbot/buildbot", "pull_number": 8869, "instance_id": "buildbot__buildbot-8869", "issue_numbers": [3104], "base_commit": "b79414723644b5bf0ce97627758668098cf21eee", "patch": "diff --git a/master/docs/manual/configuration/wwwhooks.rst b/master/docs/manual/configuration/wwwhooks.rst\nindex a3e96a601c0..e717a823c7d 100644\n--- a/master/docs/manual/configuration/wwwhooks.rst\n+++ b/master/docs/manual/configuration/wwwhooks.rst\n@@ -229,8 +229,11 @@ Github hook creates 3 kinds of changes, distinguishable by their ``category`` fi\n .. warning::\n \n     The incoming HTTP requests for this hook are not authenticated by default.\n-    Anyone who can access the web server can \"fake\" a request from GitHub, potentially causing the\n-    buildmaster to run arbitrary code.\n+    To prevent unauthorized requests, you should configure either a webhook\n+    ``secret`` or use the :ref:`Change-Hooks-Auth` option.\n+    \n+    When a secret is configured, Buildbot validates the GitHub webhook\n+    signature to ensure the request originated from GitHub.\n \n To protect URL against unauthorized access you should use :ref:`Change-Hooks-Auth` option.\n Then change the ``Payload URL`` of your GitHub webhook to\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "hooks: update GitHub hook documentation\nThe documentation currently says GitHub auth is not implemented, but actually it is. Generally the documentation for the GitHub webhook is outdated.\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/buildbot/buildbot/commit/2146aea4986a6c7fd8b58fcbd6bc0baf7d9da798"], "created_at": "2026-03-07T21:17:04Z"}
{"repo": "buildbot/buildbot", "pull_number": 8837, "instance_id": "buildbot__buildbot-8837", "issue_numbers": [4274], "base_commit": "6ab685890230bfd68697e088e063ebd1b489d59e", "patch": "diff --git a/newsfragments/4274.bugfix b/newsfragments/4274.bugfix\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000000..2bc4471ba6c8\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/newsfragments/4274.bugfix\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+Deleted logs now display a message indicating they have been removed instead of showing empty content (:issue:`4274`).\ndiff --git a/www/base/src/components/LogPreview/LogPreview.tsx b/www/base/src/components/LogPreview/LogPreview.tsx\nindex f6b1770255b1..e89c4b86d3ca 100644\n--- a/www/base/src/components/LogPreview/LogPreview.tsx\n+++ b/www/base/src/components/LogPreview/LogPreview.tsx\n@@ -90,6 +90,10 @@ export const LogPreview = observer(\n         return;\n       }\n \n+      if (log.type === 'd') {\n+        return;\n+      }\n+\n       if (log.type === 'h') {\n         if (pendingRequest.current !== null) {\n           pendingRequest.current.cancel();\n@@ -158,6 +162,9 @@ export const LogPreview = observer(\n     }, [log.num_lines, fullDisplay]);\n \n     const renderLogContent = () => {\n+      if (log.type === 'd') {\n+        return <Card.Body>This log has been deleted from the database.</Card.Body>;\n+      }\n       if (log.type === 'h') {\n         return <Card.Body dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{__html: htmlLog}} />;\n       }\n@@ -197,13 +204,19 @@ export const LogPreview = observer(\n             </div>\n             <div className=\"flex-grow-1\">\n               <div className=\"bb-log-preview-download\">\n-                <Link\n-                  to={`/builders/${builderid}/builds/${buildnumber}/steps/${stepnumber}/logs/${log.slug}`}\n-                >\n-                  view all {log.num_lines} line{log.num_lines > 1 ? 's' : ''}\n-                  &nbsp;\n-                </Link>\n-                <LogDownloadButtons log={log} />\n+                {log.type !== 'd' ? (\n+                  <>\n+                    <Link\n+                      to={`/builders/${builderid}/builds/${buildnumber}/steps/${stepnumber}/logs/${log.slug}`}\n+                    >\n+                      view all {log.num_lines} line{log.num_lines > 1 ? 's' : ''}\n+                      &nbsp;\n+                    </Link>\n+                    <LogDownloadButtons log={log} />\n+                  </>\n+                ) : (\n+                  <span className=\"text-muted\">deleted</span>\n+                )}\n               </div>\n             </div>\n           </div>\ndiff --git a/www/base/src/components/LogViewer/LogViewer.tsx b/www/base/src/components/LogViewer/LogViewer.tsx\nindex cf71df0d41a1..835684d8e08f 100644\n--- a/www/base/src/components/LogViewer/LogViewer.tsx\n+++ b/www/base/src/components/LogViewer/LogViewer.tsx\n@@ -24,6 +24,9 @@ export type LogViewerProps = {\n };\n \n export const LogViewer = ({log}: LogViewerProps) => {\n+  if (log.type === 'd') {\n+    return <p>This log has been deleted from the database.</p>;\n+  }\n   if (log.type === 'h') {\n     return <LogViewerHtml log={log} />;\n   } else {\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Deleted logs are not properly displayed in the UI.\ndeleted logs have type 'd'.\r\n\r\nCurrently this is displaying empty log, while it should be displaying that the log has expired and has been deleted from the db.\r\n\n", "hints_text": "@tardyp I'm looking forward to contributing to this project and would like to take up this issue.\r\nI'm a newbie and I'm trying to set up by going through the info on http://trac.buildbot.net/wiki/RunningBuildbotWithVirtualEnv\r\nPlease, spare some time and let me know how to get started with this\nHi. Thanks for willing to contribute to the project. The UI workflow is a little bit different\r\n\r\nYou can find a tutorial on how to work with the UI here:\r\nhttps://medium.com/buildbot/buildbot-ui-plugin-for-python-developer-ef9dcfdedac0\n@tardyp  I want to work on this but would like some help here on setup\nAll documentation on developer setup is available here:\r\nhttps://docs.buildbot.net/current/developer/quickstart.html\r\n\r\nplease tell what is your actual pain point so that we can help\n@tardyp Hey, can I work on this issue.\nNo problem.\r\n\r\nLe sam. 7 oct. 2023, 02:11, jdsk1899 ***@***.***> a \u00e9crit :\r\n\r\n> @tardyp <https://github.com/tardyp> Hey, can I work on this issue.\r\n>\r\n> \u2014\r\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\r\n> <https://github.com/buildbot/buildbot/issues/4274#issuecomment-1751518433>,\r\n> or unsubscribe\r\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AAA22I7ZNIMVTU3CY7P2V53X6CM4TAVCNFSM4FRLR4VKU5DIOJSWCZC7NNSXTN2JONZXKZKDN5WW2ZLOOQ5TCNZVGE2TCOBUGMZQ>\r\n> .\r\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.Message ID:\r\n> ***@***.***>\r\n>\r\n\nIs this issue up for grabs? I would like to contribute\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@tardyp I'm looking forward to contributing to this project and would like to take up this issue.\r\nI'm a newbie and I'm trying to set up by going through the info on http://trac.buildbot.net/wiki/RunningBuildbotWithVirtualEnv\r\nPlease, spare some time and let me know how to get started with this\nHi. Thanks for willing to contribute to the project. The UI workflow is a little bit different\r\n\r\nYou can find a tutorial on how to work with the UI here:\r\nhttps://medium.com/buildbot/buildbot-ui-plugin-for-python-developer-ef9dcfdedac0\n@tardyp  I want to work on this but would like some help here on setup\nAll documentation on developer setup is available here:\r\nhttps://docs.buildbot.net/current/developer/quickstart.html\r\n\r\nplease tell what is your actual pain point so that we can help\n@tardyp Hey, can I work on this issue.\nNo problem.\r\n\r\nLe sam. 7 oct. 2023, 02:11, jdsk1899 ***@***.***> a \u00e9crit :\r\n\r\n> @tardyp <https://github.com/tardyp> Hey, can I work on this issue.\r\n>\r\n> \u2014\r\n> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub\r\n> <https://github.com/buildbot/buildbot/issues/4274#issuecomment-1751518433>,\r\n> or unsubscribe\r\n> <https://github.com/notifications/unsubscribe-auth/AAA22I7ZNIMVTU3CY7P2V53X6CM4TAVCNFSM4FRLR4VKU5DIOJSWCZC7NNSXTN2JONZXKZKDN5WW2ZLOOQ5TCNZVGE2TCOBUGMZQ>\r\n> .\r\n> You are receiving this because you were mentioned.Message ID:\r\n> ***@***.***>\r\n>\r\n\nIs this issue up for grabs? I would like to contribute\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/buildbot/buildbot/commit/94b7059934aa265f63659f9165ff58199e6c12a9"], "created_at": "2026-03-03T19:20:08Z"}
{"repo": "buildbot/buildbot", "pull_number": 8980, "instance_id": "buildbot__buildbot-8980", "issue_numbers": [5007], "base_commit": "2acb0121a9d6bad4232db032f9e9f5d497ae029a", "patch": "diff --git a/master/buildbot/www/config.py b/master/buildbot/www/config.py\nindex 136aff5641eb..09e22ce449df 100644\n--- a/master/buildbot/www/config.py\n+++ b/master/buildbot/www/config.py\n@@ -93,18 +93,40 @@ def to_json(obj: Any) -> dict[str, Any] | str:\n \n \n _known_theme_variables = (\n+    (\"bb-avatar-bg-color\", \"#ccc\"),\n+    (\"bb-background-color\", \"#fff\"),\n+    (\"bb-border-color\", \"#ddd\"),\n+    (\"bb-btn-background-color\", \"#fff\"),\n+    (\"bb-btn-border-color\", \"#ccc\"),\n+    (\"bb-btn-hover-background-color\", \"#e6e6e6\"),\n+    (\"bb-btn-hover-border-color\", \"#adadad\"),\n+    (\"bb-card-bg-color\", \"#f5f5f5\"),\n+    (\"bb-card-border-color\", \"#ddd\"),\n+    (\"bb-card-header-text-color\", \"#333\"),\n+    (\"bb-dropdown-bg-color\", \"#f7f7f7\"),\n+    (\"bb-dropdown-border-color\", \"#ebebeb\"),\n+    (\"bb-dropdown-hover-bg-color\", \"#f5f5f5\"),\n+    (\"bb-highlight-border-color\", \"#ffff00\"),\n+    (\"bb-home-card-header-bg-color\", \"#337ab7\"),\n+    (\"bb-link-color\", \"#337ab7\"),\n+    (\"bb-muted-text-color\", \"#555\"),\n+    (\"bb-navbar-separator-color\", \"#ccc\"),\n+    (\"bb-panel-separator-bg-color\", \"#ddd\"),\n     (\"bb-sidebar-background-color\", \"#30426a\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-header-background-color\", \"#273759\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-header-text-color\", \"#fff\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-title-text-color\", \"#627cb7\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-footer-background-color\", \"#273759\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-button-text-color\", \"#b2bfdc\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-button-hover-background-color\", \"#1b263d\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-button-hover-text-color\", \"#fff\"),\n     (\"bb-sidebar-button-current-background-color\", \"#273759\"),\n     (\"bb-sidebar-button-current-text-color\", \"#b2bfdc\"),\n-    (\"bb-sidebar-stripe-hover-color\", \"#e99d1a\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-button-hover-background-color\", \"#1b263d\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-button-hover-text-color\", \"#fff\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-button-text-color\", \"#b2bfdc\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-footer-background-color\", \"#273759\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-header-background-color\", \"#273759\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-header-text-color\", \"#fff\"),\n     (\"bb-sidebar-stripe-current-color\", \"#8c5e10\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-stripe-hover-color\", \"#e99d1a\"),\n+    (\"bb-sidebar-title-text-color\", \"#627cb7\"),\n+    (\"bb-tag-active-bg-color\", \"#5cb85c\"),\n+    (\"bb-tag-bg-color\", \"#777\"),\n+    (\"bb-text-color\", \"#333\"),\n )\n \n \ndiff --git a/master/docs/manual/configuration/www/server.rst b/master/docs/manual/configuration/www/server.rst\nindex 0e4ce0ffd012..0a6d4f8b844f 100644\n--- a/master/docs/manual/configuration/www/server.rst\n+++ b/master/docs/manual/configuration/www/server.rst\n@@ -184,6 +184,7 @@ This server is configured with the ``www`` configuration key, which specifies a\n \n         c['www']['ui_default_config'] = {\n             'Builders.buildFetchLimit': 500,\n+            'Appearance.theme': 'Dark',\n         }\n \n ``ws_ping_interval``\n@@ -206,18 +207,40 @@ This server is configured with the ``www`` configuration key, which specifies a\n     .. code-block:: python\n \n         c[\"www\"][\"theme\"] = {\n+            \"bb-avatar-bg-color\": \"#ccc\",\n+            \"bb-background-color\": \"#fff\",\n+            \"bb-border-color\": \"#ddd\",\n+            \"bb-btn-background-color\": \"#fff\",\n+            \"bb-btn-border-color\": \"#ccc\",\n+            \"bb-btn-hover-background-color\": \"#e6e6e6\",\n+            \"bb-btn-hover-border-color\": \"#adadad\",\n+            \"bb-card-bg-color\": \"#f5f5f5\",\n+            \"bb-card-border-color\": \"#ddd\",\n+            \"bb-card-header-text-color\": \"#333\",\n+            \"bb-dropdown-bg-color\": \"#f7f7f7\",\n+            \"bb-dropdown-border-color\": \"#ebebeb\",\n+            \"bb-dropdown-hover-bg-color\": \"#f5f5f5\",\n+            \"bb-highlight-border-color\": \"#ffff00\",\n+            \"bb-home-card-header-bg-color\": \"#337ab7\",\n+            \"bb-link-color\": \"#337ab7\",\n+            \"bb-muted-text-color\": \"#555\",\n+            \"bb-navbar-separator-color\": \"#ccc\",\n+            \"bb-panel-separator-bg-color\": \"#ddd\",\n             \"bb-sidebar-background-color\": \"#30426a\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-header-background-color\": \"#273759\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-header-text-color\": \"#fff\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-title-text-color\": \"#627cb7\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-footer-background-color\": \"#273759\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-button-text-color\": \"#b2bfdc\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-button-hover-background-color\": \"#1b263d\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-button-hover-text-color\": \"#fff\",\n             \"bb-sidebar-button-current-background-color\": \"#273759\",\n             \"bb-sidebar-button-current-text-color\": \"#b2bfdc\",\n-            \"bb-sidebar-stripe-hover-color\": \"#e99d1a\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-button-hover-background-color\": \"#1b263d\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-button-hover-text-color\": \"#fff\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-button-text-color\": \"#b2bfdc\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-footer-background-color\": \"#273759\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-header-background-color\": \"#273759\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-header-text-color\": \"#fff\",\n             \"bb-sidebar-stripe-current-color\": \"#8c5e10\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-stripe-hover-color\": \"#e99d1a\",\n+            \"bb-sidebar-title-text-color\": \"#627cb7\",\n+            \"bb-tag-active-bg-color\": \"#5cb85c\",\n+            \"bb-tag-bg-color\": \"#777\",\n+            \"bb-text-color\": \"#333\",\n         }\n \n .. note::\ndiff --git a/newsfragments/5007.feature b/newsfragments/5007.feature\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 000000000000..197beacd1e3f\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/newsfragments/5007.feature\n@@ -0,0 +1,1 @@\n+Added dark theme support to the web UI. A new \"Appearance\" setting allows switching between Light and Dark themes. All CSS hardcoded colors have been replaced with CSS custom properties for full theme support (:issue:`5007`).\ndiff --git a/www/base/index.html b/www/base/index.html\nindex 0b1d8aef0a36..0db432eeb978 100644\n--- a/www/base/index.html\n+++ b/www/base/index.html\n@@ -15,18 +15,40 @@\n          - the actual color generation at master/buildbot/www/config.py _known_theme_variables\n       */\n       :root {\n+        --bb-avatar-bg-color: #ccc;\n+        --bb-background-color: #fff;\n+        --bb-border-color: #ddd;\n+        --bb-btn-background-color: #fff;\n+        --bb-btn-border-color: #ccc;\n+        --bb-btn-hover-background-color: #e6e6e6;\n+        --bb-btn-hover-border-color: #adadad;\n+        --bb-card-bg-color: #f5f5f5;\n+        --bb-card-border-color: #ddd;\n+        --bb-card-header-text-color: #333;\n+        --bb-dropdown-bg-color: #f7f7f7;\n+        --bb-dropdown-border-color: #ebebeb;\n+        --bb-dropdown-hover-bg-color: #f5f5f5;\n+        --bb-highlight-border-color: #ffff00;\n+        --bb-home-card-header-bg-color: #337ab7;\n+        --bb-link-color: #337ab7;\n+        --bb-muted-text-color: #555;\n+        --bb-navbar-separator-color: #ccc;\n+        --bb-panel-separator-bg-color: #ddd;\n         --bb-sidebar-background-color: #30426a;\n-        --bb-sidebar-header-background-color: #273759;\n-        --bb-sidebar-header-text-color: #fff;\n-        --bb-sidebar-title-text-color: #627cb7;\n-        --bb-sidebar-footer-background-color: #273759;\n-        --bb-sidebar-button-text-color: #b2bfdc;\n-        --bb-sidebar-button-hover-background-color: #1b263d;\n-        --bb-sidebar-button-hover-text-color: #fff;\n         --bb-sidebar-button-current-background-color: #273759;\n         --bb-sidebar-button-current-text-color: #b2bfdc;\n-        --bb-sidebar-stripe-hover-color: #e99d1a;\n+        --bb-sidebar-button-hover-background-color: #1b263d;\n+        --bb-sidebar-button-hover-text-color: #fff;\n+        --bb-sidebar-button-text-color: #b2bfdc;\n+        --bb-sidebar-footer-background-color: #273759;\n+        --bb-sidebar-header-background-color: #273759;\n+        --bb-sidebar-header-text-color: #fff;\n         --bb-sidebar-stripe-current-color: #8c5e10;\n+        --bb-sidebar-stripe-hover-color: #e99d1a;\n+        --bb-sidebar-title-text-color: #627cb7;\n+        --bb-tag-active-bg-color: #5cb85c;\n+        --bb-tag-bg-color: #777;\n+        --bb-text-color: #333;\n       }\n     </style>\n     <!-- BUILDBOT_THEME_CSS_PLACEHOLDER_END -->\ndiff --git a/www/base/src/components/BuildSummary/BuildSummary.scss b/www/base/src/components/BuildSummary/BuildSummary.scss\nindex 144955388182..7d4bea54f302 100644\n--- a/www/base/src/components/BuildSummary/BuildSummary.scss\n+++ b/www/base/src/components/BuildSummary/BuildSummary.scss\n@@ -2,9 +2,9 @@\n \n .bb-build-summary {\n   .card-header {\n-    color: #333333;\n-    background-color: #f5f5f5;\n-    border-color: #ddd;\n+    color: var(--bb-card-header-text-color);\n+    background-color: var(--bb-card-bg-color);\n+    border-color: var(--bb-card-border-color);\n     padding: 0.375rem 1rem;\n     border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;\n     border-top-left-radius: 3px;\n@@ -29,9 +29,9 @@\n   }\n \n   .btn-default {\n-    color: #333;\n-    background-color: #fff;\n-    border-color: #ccc;\n+    color: var(--bb-text-color);\n+    background-color: var(--bb-btn-background-color);\n+    border-color: var(--bb-btn-border-color);\n   }\n \n   .group-results > li .bb-build-request-summary > div {\n@@ -48,7 +48,7 @@\n   }\n \n   &.list-group-item.bb-anchor-target {\n-    border: 2px solid #ffff00;\n+    border: 2px solid var(--bb-highlight-border-color);\n   }\n   .bb-build-summary-step-anchor-link {\n     display: none;\ndiff --git a/www/base/src/components/MultipleWorkersActionsModal/